[assistant] Refined `BCGOST3410PublicKeyTest` to more directly exercise the uncovered serialization call sites.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Changes in:
[assistant] - `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk15to18/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk15to18/BCGOST3410PublicKeyTest.java`
[assistant] 
[assistant] What changed:
[assistant] - Added a plain Java serialization round-trip test using standard `ObjectOutputStream.writeObject(...)` and `ObjectInputStream.readObject()`.
[assistant] - Kept the parameter-observing serialization test to verify `BCGOST3410PublicKey.writeObject/readObject` write and read the GOST parameter OIDs.
[assistant] - Switched key construction to public JCA `KeyFactory` with Bouncy Castle provider and `X509EncodedKeySpec`, backed by a valid `SubjectPublicKeyInfo` containing the CryptoPro-A and digest OIDs.
[assistant] - Avoided the earlier raw-parameter construction path that creates a key without a parameter-set OID and can break `getEncoded()`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I did not run the Gradle test command, per the workflow rule.
